    {
        "content": "<p>github-actions[bot] <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974#issuecomment-4195633064\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974\">PR #12974</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h4>Subscribe to Label Action</h4>\n<p>cc @fitzgen</p>\n<p>&lt;details&gt;<br>\nThis issue or pull request has been labeled: \"wasmtime:api\", \"wasmtime:ref-types\"</p>\n<p>Thus the following users have been cc'd because of the following labels:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>fitzgen: wasmtime:ref-types</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To subscribe or unsubscribe from this label, edit the &lt;code&gt;.github/subscribe-to-label.json&lt;/code&gt; configuration file.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/subscribe-to-label-action\">Learn more.</a><br>\n&lt;/details&gt;</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 583886358,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775519643
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974#pullrequestreview-4071218189\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I need to spend more time looking at <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974/changes/a6badd88b3ca0e944848e0b9c96bf80303b35d3e\">Combine dec_ref, trace, and dealloc into single-pass loop</a> but this is one thing I noticed. The later commits seem fine though.</p>\n<p>This is another case though where in-wasm GC allocation, GC mark/sweep, etc, would I suspect remove a huge amount of the overhead since the host has to dance around \"the heap could be corrupt at any time\" which loses a lot of perf I believe. I realize that's a big undertaking, but we may want to discuss more seriously in a meeting at some point if it's table stakes or not for shipping gc.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 584083979,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775595388
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974#discussion_r3047795746\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This seems like it's a bit of a poor-man's hash map here. Since this is already using a hash map, what's the performance of using a custom hasher where the hash of <code>VMSharedTypeIndex</code> is just its bit value?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 584083980,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775595389
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974#issuecomment-4202270767\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974\">PR #12974</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I realize that's a big undertaking, but we may want to discuss more seriously in a meeting at some point if it's table stakes or not for shipping gc.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Happy to discuss at a meeting, I'll add an item, but I find it super surprising that we would even entertain the idea of blocking enabling the GC proposal by default on self-hosting the free list (or even worse from a time-to-shipping perspective: self-hosting the whole collector runtime).</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 584087106,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775596798
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974#pullrequestreview-4076744307\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>@fitzgen @cfallin and I talked a bit more about GC things today, and we'll summarize our thinking at tomorrow's Wasmtime meeting as well.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 584271105,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775666727
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974#pullrequestreview-4078935947\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 584331004,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775691285
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12974#discussion_r3054728932\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Good call. I reverted that commit and things got ~10% slower, but then I added a custom nop-hasher and they got ~3% faster from where we started. So seems like the nop-hasher is the way to go! Will push momentarily.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 584331007,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775691286
    },
